s on targeting, flighting, and campaign objectives based on marketing goals Identifies and evaluates new digital technologies Helps prioritize marketing initiatives and opportunities Uses Web analytics tools to measure site traffic to better optimize marketing campaigns, email marketing, social media and display and search advertising Participate in brainstorms and help execute planned content Requirements Strong advocate for Swing Left\u2019s mission Bachelor\u2019s Degree from an accredited institution and 3-5 years professional experience in a marketing or advertising role. Strategic thinker who can provide new creative solutions Strong writing skills across multiple channels. Ability to draft sharp, concise content and distill complex issues into vivid, understandable language. Willingness to learn and a quick study Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to be proactive, organized, efficient and manage multiple projects under deadline pressure with great accuracy; strong project management skills and ability to manage external consultants. Ability to multi-task and shift between priorities Understanding of marketing campaign development and the various mediums and channels to execute a campaign: video, website, social, digital marketing, email, paid advertising. Experience collaborating with marketing and creative departments Detail-oriented with strong organizational skills and the ability to meet deadlines Comfortable reading data and understanding how to make recommendations based on the reporting Demonstrates initiative and follow-through We are an equal opportunity employer and seek applications from all qualified candidates who are eligible to work in the United States. However, we are not able to sponsor visas at this time. The Digital Marketing Specialist position is a full-time, remote position. Swing Left provides a competitive salary and benefits package. We are happy to answer any questions you have about our benefits, retirement, parental leave policies and other, similar benefits in interviews. We believe that the GOP\u2019s bad behavior disproportionately hurts the most marginalized people in society \u2014 including people of color, people from working-class backgrounds, people with disabilities, women and LGBTQ people. We believe that these communities must be centered in the work we do. Hence, we strongly encourage applications from people with these identities and members of other marginalized communities. If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of theÂ requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs College Fellow Fall 2020 Swingleft We can beat Trump and the GOP, if we get started now. Enter your zip code and find things to do now to help Democrats win the 2020 elections. Anywhere Full Time Posted 4 weeks ago Performance Marketing Manager Komoot Change The Way People Explore Anywhere Full Time Posted 4 weeks ago Performance Marketing Manager Komoot Change The Way People Explore Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 months ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewoman.com @ 2020 RemoteWoman \u2014 All Rights Reserved My account Post a job Back to Top Marketing Developer Design Product Sales Support"
